Non-Discrimination
Dermstore will not discriminate against you because you exercise your rights. For example, Dermstore will not deny you goods or services or charge you a different price or rate for goods or services if you make an access, deletion, or do not sell request.
Loyalty Program
Dermstore Rewards is a voluntary loyalty program that provides you with 5% back on purchases, ability to redeem points without brand exclusions, surprise birthday gift and access to members-only events. By joining Dermstore Rewards program, you receive:
Earn 5% back on purchases: You earn 5 points for every dollar you spend on Dermstore.com
Redeem points without brand exclusions
Surprise Birthday Gift
Access to members-only events
*Terms and restrictions apply to the 5% rewards. Visit
dermstore.com/rewards
for details.
**Some restrictions apply. Program rules are available at
dermstore.com/rewards
Under the CCPA, Dermstore Rewards is considered a Financial Incentive Program. In order to provide you with the incentives described above, we use personal information about you including your name, phone number, email address, purchase history, birthdate, etc. to identify you as a member of the program and provide you with relevant messaging, experiences and deals. These financial incentives are reasonably related to the value of the data you provide.
We incur a variety of expenses related to the Dermstore Rewards program. We make this investment in order to offer a more personalized and relevant customer experience. Expense associated with the program include the earnings when you shopped at Dermstore, access to deals only available to Rewards members, and bonus earnings. The expense associated with the program incentives will vary as it is dependent on your engagement with the Rewards program, including total annual spend at Dermstore and frequency and depth of discounts you choose to use.
Categories of Personal Information implicated by Dermstore Rewards:
Identifiers (e.g. name, mailing address, email address, phone number, credit/debit card number)
Characteristics of protected classifications (e.g. gender, age)
Commercial information (e.g. products or services purchased, purchase history)
Internet or other electronic network activity (e.g. browse or search history)
Inferences drawn from any of the above (e.g. preferences or characteristics)
There are a couple ways to become a Dermstore Rewards member. When you create a new account, you will be opted into the Dermstore Rewards program unless you unselect the "include me in the Dermstore Rewards program" box. You can also choose to opt in and become a Dermstore Rewards member by visiting Dermstore.com/rewards.
If you no longer wish to be a Dermstore Rewards member, you can opt out of Dermstore Rewards
here
.
If you opt out of Dermstore Rewards, any accumulated Dermstore Rewards points will be deleted and you may not have access to other Dermstore Rewards benefits. If you later re-join Dermstore Rewards, any deleted Dermstore Rewards points will not be reinstated.
